            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Sorry if this sounds very obvious. \r\n\r\nSince `ArrayOf(Integer)` is a typedef for `Array`, from return value perspective, both will satisfy it. If I am not wrong `ArrayOf(...)` just makes it clearer to the consumer of the API that the return types meets the mentioned constraints.\r\n\r\nBut since we may have the items like `[Integer, Integer, Dictionary]` if `{details: true}` is passed, we have to give the return type as just `Array`.\r\n\r\nAs the checks are failing and the function expects an `ArrayOf(Integer)`, do I need to modify the test case as well?\r\n\r\nAlso I get this error while testing on my laptop regarding swap files. The expected results seems correct. Can someone please guide me on this.\r\n<details>\r\n<summary>Log</summary>\r\n<pre>\r\n<code>\r\n-------- Running tests from test/functional/ex_cmds/swapfile_preserve_recover_spec.lua <br/>\r\nRUN      T1953 :recover fails if given a non-existent swapfile: 6.79 ms OK <br/>\r\nRUN      T1954 :preserve saves to custom 'directory' and (R)ecovers #1836: 22.37 ms OK <br/>\r\nRUN      T1955 swapfile detection always show swapfile dialog #8840 #9027: 98.72 ms OK <br/>\r\nRUN      T1956 swapfile detection selecting \"q\" in the attention prompt: 44.48 ms OK <br/>\r\nRUN      T1957 swapfile detection allows deleting swapfile created before boot vim-patch:8.2.2586: 3524.88 ms FAIL <br/>\r\ntest/functional/ex_cmds/swapfile_preserve_recover_spec.lua:316: Failed to match any screen lines. <br/>\r\nExpected (anywhere): \"{2:E325: ATTENTION}.*file name: .*Xswaptest.*process ID: %d* %(STILL RUNNING%).*{1:%[O%]pen Read%-Only, %(E%)dit anyway, %(R%)ecover, %(Q%)uit, %(A%)bort: }%^\" <br/>\r\nActual: <br/>\r\n  |                                                                           | <br/>\r\n  |{0:~                                                                          }| <br/>\r\n  |{UNEXPECTED bold = true, reverse = true:                                                                           }| <br/>\r\n  |{2:E325: ATTENTION}                                                            | <br/>\r\n  |Found a swap file by the name \"~/neovim/X| <br/>\r\n  |test_swapdialog_dir//%Users%neovim%| <br/>\r\n  |Xswaptest.swp\"                                                             | <br/>\r\n  |          owned by: user   dated: Thu Jan 12 07:29:21 2023                | <br/>\r\n  |         file name: ~/neovim/Xswapte| <br/>\r\n  |st                                                                         | <br/>\r\n  |          modified: YES                                                    | <br/>\r\n  |         user name:    host name: hostname                          | <br/>\r\n  |        process ID: 8229 (STILL RUNNING)                                   | <br/>\r\n  |While opening file \"Xswaptest\"                                             | <br/>\r\n  |      CANNOT BE FOUND                                                      | <br/>\r\n  |(1) Another program may be editing the same file.  If this is the case,    | <br/>\r\n  |    be careful not to end up with two different instances of the same      | <br/>\r\n  |    file when making changes.  Quit, or continue with caution.             | <br/>\r\n  |(2) An edit session for this file crashed.                                 | <br/>\r\n  |    If this is the case, use \":recover\" or \"vim -r Xswaptest\"              | <br/>\r\n  |    to recover the changes (see \":help recovery\").                         | <br/>\r\n  |    If you did this already, delete the swap file \"/Users/| <br/>\r\n  |neovim/Xtest_swapdialog_dir//%Users%| <br/>\r\n  |neovim%Xswaptest.swp\"                              | <br/>\r\n  |    to avoid this message.                                                 | <br/>\r\n  |                                                                           | <br/>\r\n  |{1:Swap file \"~/neovim/Xtest_swapdialog_dir/}| <br/>\r\n  |{1:/%Users%neovim%Xswaptest.swp\" alrea}| <br/>\r\n  |{1:dy exists!}                                                                 | <br/>\r\n  |{1:[O]pen Read-Only, (E)dit anyway, (R)ecover, (Q)uit, (A)bort: }^              | <br/>\r\n <br/>\r\n <br/>\r\n <br/>\r\nstack traceback: <br/>\r\n\ttest/functional/ui/screen.lua:604: in function '_wait' <br/>\r\n\ttest/functional/ui/screen.lua:351: in function 'expect' <br/>\r\n\ttest/functional/ex_cmds/swapfile_preserve_recover_spec.lua:316: in function <test/functional/ex_cmds/swapfile_preserve_recover_spec.lua:270> <br/>\r\n</code>\r\n</pre>\r\n</details>",
